# shoot-scheduling-api — project context

A legacy scheduling API for booking soundstages for shoots. Real tech debt on purpose for
brownfield agent practice.

## Architecture

`src/server.ts` wires Express and mounts one router. `src/routes/bookings.ts` holds a
single fat handler. `src/db.ts` is an in-memory store. `src/legacy/rates.js` is untyped
JavaScript with order-dependent pricing rules. Treat the rate card as a contract.

## Known tech debt

- POST handler returns three different error shapes with three different status codes.
- No tests. `npm test` fails on purpose.
- `capacityFor` returns `undefined` for unknown stages instead of throwing.
- Rate card applies surge before volume discount — that order is the contract.

## Conventions

- TypeScript is in loose mode (`strict: false`). Do not flip strict on in passing.
- Keep handlers thin; push business logic into a service layer.
- Do not introduce a new dependency without calling it out in your summary.
- Before changing `rates.js`, write characterization tests first.
- Check `specs/constitution.md` and the relevant feature spec before implementing.
